More than 300 pastors and government officials held peace prayers for the election in Mlolongo, Machakos county, on Monday.The meeting was organised by the Association of Evangelicals in Africa. Its East Africa President, Arthur Kitonga, said the prayers were meant to cleanse Mlolongo town and preach peace in Machakos ahead of the August 8 polls.&ldquo;There are lots of dirty things happening in Mlolongo. We are told a week does not pass without reporting cases of deaths in the hands of criminals,&rdquo; he told journalists after the session.Kitonga said the town was exposed to many criminal activities, including prostitution.